<item>
            <title>[LU-13697] short io for AIO</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13697</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; It might be possible that one aio request could not be finished&lt;br/&gt;
 with one IO loop because of io request across stripes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since -EIOCBQUEUED is returned for AIO, io loop will be stopped thus short io happen.&lt;br/&gt;
There should be codes to handle these kind of cases, otherwise, fio or some other&lt;br/&gt;
applications could fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
